snippet.textDisplay: An observation in the difference between the way Rangers and Celtic play: Celtic attack and defend as a team, they always have players back supporting the defence which makes it a whole lot harder for the opposition. Rangers seem to leave their back 4 on their own, with wingers and striker staying high up the pitch meaning the opposition have it easier. We keep letting these teams threaten our goal by making it an even game in terms of numbers at the back. We need to learn to copy the way Celtic play and ask for a bit more from the whole team rather than slating the defence alone. We should be blowing teams away but individual errors and poor team work have ruined our season.
